final_output_text: To neatly cut a cake, it is important to ensure that the knife remains sharp and free of any moisture, which can cause the blade to become dull or slip. This is why the knife should be run under hot water. Running the knife under hot water helps to remove any food particles or debris that may be on the blade, which can then be dried and used for cutting. This process helps to keep the knife sharp and ensures a clean cut.

On the other hand, running the knife under cold water would not remove any debris or food particles, and it could potentially make the blade more slippery, leading to an uneven or messy cut.

Therefore, the best solution is to run the knife under hot water, dry the knife, and cut, repeating as needed. This method ensures that the knife remains sharp and clean, resulting in a neat and precise cut.

