2. **Solution 1: Run metal rods through the straws to join pieces.**  
   Metal rods are rigid and heavy compared to a bendable wire. While they can be used to join straws, their rigidity may limit the flexibility of the art, making it harder to create smooth curves and intricate polygonal shapes. Additionally, metal rods are more difficult to work with and may not be as practical for a hands-on artistic project.

