final_output_text: When working on a plumbing soldering project, it's important to ensure that the copper pipes are free of burrs before you solder them. Burrs can interfere with the soldering process and lead to weak joints. To deburr a copper pipe, you need a tool that is sharp enough to remove the burrs without damaging the pipe.

